{
  "texts": [
    "Their theoretical strength in handling long sequences was empirically validated by precursors like S4 [15] on the demanding Long Range Arena benchmark [34].",
    "Notably, on the Path-X benchmark within this suite, which requires identifying a continuous logical path from a series of visual dashes, S4 achieved a high score while Transformer-based models trained from scratch failed.",
    "The task's use of a dashed path serves as a strong proxy for real-world continuity challenges, such as tracing road networks fragmented by occlusions.",
    "This result highlights that the core SSM mechanism is inherently superior for tasks demanding long-range spatial continuity.",
    "Mamba [14] builds upon this success by introducing a selective scan mechanism that further enhances the ability to model these dependencies with lineartime complexity."
  ]
}